section.def:
lane
                (行車綫) means a lane for the passage of traffic
            within the Area;

subsection.def:
expressway
                    (快速公路) has the same meaning as in the
                Expressway Regulation;

subparagraph.content:
a person engaged in the maintenance, repair, cleaning, clearance,
                        survey, inspection, alteration or improvement of a road within the
                        Area;

a person engaged in the erection, laying, placing, maintenance,
                        testing, alteration, repair or removal of any structure, works or apparatus
                        in, on, under or over any part of a road within the Area;

a person engaged in the avoidance or prevention of an accident or
                        obtaining or giving assistance required as a result of an accident or
                        emergency;

subsection.def:
Cap. 374A (《第374A章》) means the Road Traffic
                (Construction and Maintenance of Vehicles) Regulations
                    (Cap. 374 sub. leg. A);

paragraph.content:
carries out road works, without a permit under section 16(1), within
                the Area or is in breach of a condition in a permit issued under that
                section;

subsection.def:
Figure No. 6 traffic sign (第6號圖形交通標誌)
                means a traffic sign of the type shown in Figure No. 6 prescribed in Schedule
                    1;

old requirement (舊規定) means the requirement indicated by Figure No. 6 traffic sign in
                accordance with the traffic sign and the note relating to the traffic sign in the
                pre-amended Schedule 1;

subparagraph.content:
when a green arrow is displayed vehicular traffic proceeding in the lane above
                or at the side of and in relation to which it is displayed may proceed along that
                lane;
